title: For Sale:  Don't buy from gougers, cheap mags are coming....
postcontent:
In response to Magpul's announcement a group of non-selfish gun owners has created a program they are calling "Operation Mountain Standard."  The mini-CheaperThanDirt gougers on here selling for 3 times the price they should are going to loose their market fast.  Here's the deal.  The OMS guys are asking gun owners from across the country to donate spare mags to the effort.  Those mags are being collected now.  On March 16th, they are setting up a booth in Boulder.  They will give you a pistol mag for a $10 donation or a rifle mag for $20 donation.  100% of donations will go to RMGO.

http://www.reddit.com/r/guns/comments/18z0ig/operation_mountain_standard_update/

This is what gun owners SHOULD be doing instead of trying to gouge each other and make a buck off of unwarranted panic.  If you have extras, donate them to the cause.  IF you need mags?  Wait a bit and get them cheap while donating to a cause that is fighting FOR you instead of against you.  Don't let the greedy gougers win.  Don't panic.  It'll be ok.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom Crafted Short Sword for Your Handgun
postcontent:
“Only One of It's Kind”  *Lakonia Short Sword / Dagger 
Please feel free to make a Reasonable Cash Offer. Keep in Mind the Man Hours Required to Forge and Create this Fine Sword.   (Not Produced from Stock Billet)
Designed Around the Most Beautiful Damascus Steel Produced to Date, the "Raindrop Pattern".
This Kind of Quality is Very, Very Rare. Forged from 1095 & 15N20 High Carbon Steel and folded 512 times to Enhance the Blade and Sword with Beautiful and Mesmerizing Raindrop Damascas Steel..  An Art Almost Lost Today. 
The 12 1/4” X 2” Wide Oak-Leaf Blade with a 5 3/4” Hilt gives an Overall Length of 18”.. The Level 60-62 HRC (Again you Collectors Know Just How Hard this Is) Means this is not Just a Sword for Display, but a Reliable Weapon. 
Getting away from the Absolutely Gorgeous Blade, the Guard is Embellished with Burl Walnut and Hand Tooled Solid Brass Enhanced with Micarta Spacers. The Grip is made of Naturally Dyed Rams Horn and also has Hand Filed Brass and Micarta Spacers. The Tang runs the length of the Hilt with a beautifully formed Brass Pommel. 
Last But Not Least the Entire Hilt is wrapped with Genuine Leather in the Japanese Tsukamaki Style. 
This Masterpiece of Craftmanship has Excellent Weight and Balance. A Real Joy to Handle.
The Sheath is made of High Quality Double Stitched Leather and has a riveted loop to hang on a belt.

*Lakonia, named after the region of Greece ruled by Sparta, was one of the primary weapons of the hoplite. It was second only to the spear and was used when their opponents came in close. These very small short swords featured the oak-leaf blade shape common to most Greek swords. They were not much more than daggers, but in the hands of a trained hoplite, they were unbelievably deadly.
